storyInfo: To improve their work efficiency, the Durins voted to ban the consumption of alcohol. Inam has to leave Acahualla for other affairs, and so the heavy task of upholding this ban falls on Gavial's shoulders.

attributes.content: I'll leave Acahualla and the Durins from Zeruertza to you guys.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Inam, you sure you have to go?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Don't go!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Don't be silly. I have to go.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: *whimper*... Inam... I'll miss you...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: What's with you two? You're making it sound like I'm never coming back!
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: But you said you'll be gone for a long time...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: This lord ameer candidacy is even more of a mess than that whole ruckus with the Big, Ugly Thing Zumama caused. Of course I can't promise to be back tomorrow!
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: *whimpers*...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: *sigh*
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: More and more, I'm thinking I made the right choice to become the lord ameer myself.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Anyway, Gavial, I'm counting on you to lead the Acahualla and the Zeruertza Durins while I'm gone.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: What do you need me to do, exactly?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Nothing.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: You mean, keep the status quo?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: That's right.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: This is how Acahualla's always been. As for the Durins, they've been in a hurry to build their settlement. To the point they even voted to prohibit alcohol to improve efficiency.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Prohibit alcohol? The Durins?!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Right, I was surprised too.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: But that's what they decided on. Looks like they have a sense of urgency, too.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: And going by their speed, they'll probably be finished by the time I get back.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Your job is to make sure everything stays the same, as if I never left. That's very important to everyone here.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: I get it. The Durins' settlement comes first, right?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: That's right.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: You can count on me!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (Doubtful glare)
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: By the way, I hid the Durins' brewing equipment in... (whispers).
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Do not let them find it. Understand?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Whoa, that's some hiding spot.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Huh? Where did she hide it? I wanna know!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: You've seen how crazy the Durins get whenever alcohol's involved. If I told you, it wouldn't take them long to squeeze that information out of you.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: *whimpers*...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: But in that case, wouldn't it be better to keep me out of this too?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: ...I'm leaving to rub shoulders with those guys from the Court of Sargon, after all. I have to be prepared for anything.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: If it turns out it'll be a while till I get back, the Durins will have to forgo their taste of home for just as long. And I wouldn't want to be the one to blame.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Alright, now let me go over the other things you need to keep an eye out for...
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Is this really okay, Gavial?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Hm? We're just helping the Durins look for some suitable timber. What's not okay about it?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: But Inam told us not to do anything...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Oh, I was wondering what you were going to say.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: What she meant was we aren't supposed to change the rules she set, not that we shouldn't do anything.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Besides, did you see how the Durins were at it under the blazing sun? I'd feel bad not helping them out somehow—
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Gavial, is that you?
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: Are you a Zeruertza Durin?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: That's right.
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: You lost like Stitch was before? How about I walk you back?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: No need.
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: I'm here because I have something to talk to you about.
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: Whatever it is, let's talk after we get back. This rainforest isn't all that safe.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: No, no, no. There's nowhere safer than here.
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: You see, I'm from the mead fan club...
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: So it's about the prohibition, huh?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: It's a good thing you're such a reasonable woman—
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: Hold on, no dice.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: No room for negotiation at all?
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: You guys are the ones who voted to forbid all alcohol. You got a problem with that, talk to your own people.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: But Inam kept all our equipment.
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: Uh, she never told me where she stored it—
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Really? Only she knows?
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: How could she do that? What if she forgets where she hid it? We'll never again get to taste Zeruertza's fine mead again. How irresponsible of her...
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: She's not irresponsible at all! She told Gavial where she kept the mead brewing equipment!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Oh my lord.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Hah, I knew it. There's no way Inam wouldn't leave a back-up plan.
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: Yeah, yeah—
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Ow!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Not like I'll ever tell you guys.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Alright, fine, looks like we won't get our mead today.
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: But we'll never give up!
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: Just as a city is laid brick by brick, I'll taste the whereabouts of our brewing equipment, bit by bit!
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: Good afternoon, Gavial.
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Heyas, what's up?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: We have a bit of an urgent matter on our hands, so I have no choice but to visit you here.
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: We're lacking some... necessities, and my fellows are all... fairly low in spirits. They're tormented, unable to sleep, and in pain.
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Poor fellas...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: I want to soothe their pain, which is why I've come to request your help, our most respected Gavial.
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: We should help them, Gavial!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: First off, don't you stick some weird adjective in front of my name.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Secondly, the necessities you guys are out of have gotta be mead, right?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: What a load of rubbish!
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Oh?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: How could you possibly compare that kids' drink to our noble No. 7 Whiskey?
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Well, whatever it is, you guys ain't getting a sip, so why does it matter?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Oh, cruel Gavial. How could you be so merciless?
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Before you accuse me of being merciless, can't you do something about the way you talk? It's weird.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Huh? Is it weird?
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: And here I thought it would be easier to talk to surface-dwellers if I imitated Avdotya's characters.
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Yeah, no, it doesn't work that way. Talk normal.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I'll die if I don't get any whiskey!
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Bear with it!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Gavial, would you please tell us where Inam hid the brewing tools?
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Gavial, where did she hide our distilling equipment?
attributes.name: Stubborn Durin

attributes.content: Gavial, our brewing equipment...
attributes.name: Chatty Durin

attributes.content: Hey, Gavial.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Zumama? Good to see you. Finally, someone who'll talk about something other than alcohol.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (Freezes)
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Urgh...
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I have a bad feeling about this.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (Deep breath)
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: It's about the Durins' brewing and distilling equipment...
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Why are you of all people asking about that?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: They promised me that the moment they get their equipment back, they'll send their mechanics to help me test my robots with their technology.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Give it up.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Nnuuh...
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: That said, I really didn't expect you on their side.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Who else have they talked to?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Let's see...
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: They tried Tomimi, but they got blasted out.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: They've also talked to their Great Chief Edge Eartheart and others from Zeruertza.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: They said it themselves. Aside from Avdotya, everyone's been either somewhat lax about it or at least... ambiguous.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Ambiguous?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Supposedly, they've even managed to persuade Chief Edge despite how strict he was with the ban at first. And we've both seen in Zeruertza how the alcohol there flew right off the shelves.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: This can't continue!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: We can't waste any more time with these fellas. They're the ones who banned all the booze, so of course they can unban it, too.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: But if it comes to that, they'll never finish their settlement... I don't want Acahualla to have nothing but a bunch of incomplete buildings waiting for Inam when she gets back!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: ...Wow.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: You wouldn't want to see that either, right?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: It doesn't really matter to me, but... I'll follow your lead.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Bring Tomimi here. Time for a war council.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Huh???
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: What do we do, Gavial?!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Calm down, Tomimi.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I'll go talk to Master Edge and ask him not to change his mind!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Stop. Stop! Come back!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I just talked to Gavial. It's not like Edge doesn't drink himself. It probably wouldn't be a good idea to talk to him now.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Avdotya might just be the only one who'll follow through with the ban, but since this involves the Durins' immediate benefit, she might be powerless herself.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: *whine*...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Actually, I have an idea.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Really? I knew you'd know what to do!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Don't get ahead of yourself. I can't do this on my own. I need your help.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Tomimi, send the word out to all the tribes and ask them to keep an eye on the Durins.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Huh? What are they gonna do?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: That depends on Zumama and her mission...
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: How many days has it been since we last had a sip?
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Yeah, I haven't been keeping count, you whiskey idiot. Couldn't be bothered to. All I remember is that all the men you guys sent to persuade her came back empty-handed. You guys are even more pathetic than Originium slugs.
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: What did you just say, you mead wimp?!
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: ...Let me warn you. You can insult us, but you can't insult Old Karl Mead!
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: The way I see it, you guys got brain damage from all that stinking foot odor you guys got with your whiskey!
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: You know...
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: I've always advocated for both sides to peacefully coexist.
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Get to the point, you berry tomato wine freak.
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Actually, my guys have almost persuaded Master Edge. We just need to wait a couple more days. Just a few more days—
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Hey there, my conspirators. Nice to see you guys.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Gavial?!
attributes.name: Booze-loving Durins

attributes.content: I'm here to talk conditions.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: What conditions?
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: I know you guys want your booze making tools, and you can't wait to get your hands on them, right?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: True enough.
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: I'll give you guys a way out, then.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: If you guys manage to beat me, I'll give you your tools back.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Really? Get her, boys—
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: Just like that?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Uhh... I guess we'll need to make some preparations first.
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: Good call.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I'll say this again. If one of you manages to defeat me, I'll give that person the tools back.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Hey, you there. That's right. You.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: An ambush isn't gonna work on me.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Anyone who tries might just end up having to give up drinking for the rest of their life.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Eek!
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Besides, ambushes are kinda underhanded, wouldn't you agree?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: W-We aren't going to bow down to you!
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Good, you've got some backbone. I'd expect no less from the newest residents of Acahualla.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Now hurry up with your preparations. I'm ready when you are!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Zumama, how are things going on your end?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Very well.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: At first, they thought they could take you on just by working a little harder and putting some gear together. Clearly they underestimated you.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: But after you handed their asses to them every single time, they started looking for another way, and it didn't take much work for me to divert their attention to robotics.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: I lent them the blueprints for the Big, Ugly Thing and had a bit of a technological exchange with them. I have to say, the Durins' technology is really interesting.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: Their self-driving carts may act like they might as well be blind, but the technology behind them is nothing to scoff at. Once deployed, we'll be in for quite a show.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: That's not a bad thing... but what I'm worried about is them putting together a self-driving Big, Ugly Thing.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Well...
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: I think that's exactly what they have in mind.
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: (Shrugs)
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Alright, fine. We were going to take this chance to see if the Durins would put together some kind of machine they could use in construction anyway.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: And I mean, they haven't really been putting up much of a fight the last few days. Getting to fight something like the Big, Ugly Thing again isn't so bad.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Bad news, Gavial!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Huh? What's the matter? Did the Durins start fighting among themselves over their booze?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Yeah, the mead fan club almost had an all-out brawl with the No. 7 Whiskey fans—
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: No, that's not what I'm here about!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: They put together a robot just as awesome as the Big, Ugly Thing, and they're testing out its weapons right now!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Oh.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: That's exactly what Zumama's mission was. Don't you remember?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Oh... I guess I worried too much.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Alright, I'll keep watching them test their weapons, then! It's like, kaboom! It looks really amazing!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Alright. Let me know if something seems off—
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Hold up, where are they doing this testing?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: At a cave not far north of the Eunectes tribe. There's nothing but trees there.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: A cave north of... the Eunectes tribe—
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Dammit!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Tomimi, hurry up and stop them. Zumama and I will be there soon!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: They're just testing weapons. Why are you so worried about it all of a sudden?
attributes.name: Eunectes

attributes.content: That's the cave where Inam hid all their alcohol making equipment!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Hah—*yawn*.
attributes.name: Not Very Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: G-Gavial?!
attributes.name: Not Very Astute Durin

attributes.content: Hey, fellas. Mind testing your weapons somewhere else?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Why should we?
attributes.name: Not Very Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Well...
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: You're the one who told us you'll give us back our tools if we defeat you!
attributes.name: Not Very Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: That I did say.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Then why are you trying to stop us?
attributes.name: Not Very Astute Durin

attributes.content: Well—That's not what I'm here for. I just want you guys to go someplace else to test your... your...
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Giant, Ultimate Ugly Thing Mk. 3!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Right. I just wanted you guys to test out the Giant, Ultimate Ugly Thing Mk. 3 somewhere else, that's all.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: This is the most suitable place we found.
attributes.name: Not Very Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Besides, we've already paid such a heavy price just to defeat you!
attributes.name: Not Very Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: What price?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: We've toiled through three whole days and nights, but that's not even important.
attributes.name: Not Very Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: What's important is we're reduced to working with these mead wimps!
attributes.name: Not Very Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: That's right! We're even working with these whiskey idiots!
attributes.name: Not Very Astute Durin

attributes.content: Oh... so that's the most important part, huh?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Anyway, we've already sacrificed so much. There's no way we're going to give up just because of what you said!
attributes.name: Not Very Astute Durin

attributes.content: All I'm asking is for you to find someplace else.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: No means no!
attributes.name: Not Very Astute Durin

attributes.content: Why's that?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (Whispers) You can't blame them, Gavial.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Whispers) Avdotya asked them to find somewhere they wouldn't bother anyone. She even threatened to not write ads for their drinks anymore if they disturbed anyone.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Whispers) That's how they ended up here.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Whispers) And I saw lots of equipment and machinery already mounted in place. They can't take them away anymore.
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Whispers) What a headache...
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (Whispers) How about I ask them not to hit the cave when they test fire their weapons...?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: That's basically giving it away that there's something there!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: *whine*...
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Now, please leave. Stop bothering us here!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Or are you trying to interfere because you think you're no match for the Giant, Ultimate Ugly Thing Mk. 3?!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Now that, I can't pretend I didn't hear.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: A-Anyway, just leave already!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: I'll say this again. I'm asking you guys to move somewhere else for your own benefit.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: We aren't going anywhere!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Ugh—What a pain.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: How about this. We'll fight here and now. How's that?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (Whispers) What are you thinking?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: (Whispers) Instead of letting them stay and blow up the cave, I might as well take the situation into my own hands. Don't worry.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: But we haven't properly tuned our weapons yet...
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: If I lose, I'll give you all your tools back. If I win, you guys still get to fight me again later. You've got nothing to lose.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I... I suppose?
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Gavial quickly runs to the south of the enormous machine.
Hey, why did you come over here?!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: That's a cave and a cliff over there. I gotta give myself some room, right?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Alright, makes sense.
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: How about we get started, then?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: W-We aren't gonna hold back!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Well, that thing sure packs some firepower. I can barely get any closer.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: That's not all! Durin Tree Trunk Saw, activate!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Hell yeah!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: But not enough!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: What?! She stopped the maximum turbo engine all by herself?!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Shit! Parry! Parry immediately!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: They dodged it?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: That's quite an agile design. You ever thought about using that to build your settlement?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Let's hear you say that after this!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Take this!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Ohh!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: She blocked an artillery shell with her axe?!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Zumama forged this for me. A couple of artillery shells? Piece of cake.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Now it's my turn!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Crap! Fall back! Fall back right now!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Not happening! Here comes the saw!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Why are we falling back? We should be parrying to the side!
attributes.name: Not Very Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: No, we should push forward. That's the only way we can dodge her saw's attacks!
attributes.name: Not Very Astute Durin

attributes.content: Stop! Stop trying to take the controller—
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: What a strange movement pattern... Why did it get behind me?!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Settle down, you two! We almost lost right there!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: You have nowhere to run, Gavial! Take my ultimate attack—
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Durin Out-of-Control Guided Missiles Omnidirectional Bombardment!!!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Crap! The cave!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Why an omnidirectional bombardment, now of all times?!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Gavial takes a deep breath, relaxes her tail, and drops her saw on the ground.
She grips the large axe with both hands.
Haah!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: What?! H-How high did she jump?!
attributes.name: Not Very Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Gavial leaps into the air and hops onto gigantic machine's leg, then its chest.
With the robot's surface as a stepping stone, Gavial once again springs up and curls her tail around its raised robotic arm, swinging towards the cave's entrance on the other side.
*Brrrr*–
Gavial looks at the artillery shells all over the ground and raises the giant axe in her hand.
Hah... hah...
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Good thing that was omnidirectional, and none of them headed this way...
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: And I also gotta thank you guys for not putting any explosives in the missiles... At least you knew to hold back there...
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: *belch*
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I have no idea why you care about that cave so much, but now that you've had a taste of our missiles, there's no way you can stand anymore!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: The missiles are filled with Archosaurian booze. Even those with the highest tolerance amongst us can't stay on their feet after getting blasted by one of these!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Urgh...
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: So... Does it look like I'm lying on the ground right now?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: No way...
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: How come the missile didn't work on you?
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: I mean, how much booze did you put in the missiles anyway? It's not like I drank any. Breathing in that little bit just makes you tipsy at most. Why would anyone fall down and not be able to get up?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: But none of us could...
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: That just goes to show what a bunch of lightweights you guys are.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: (Facepalms)
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Set that aside for now! Why are you so worried about the cave, Gavial?! Are you hiding something in there that's stopping us from getting our tools back?!
attributes.name: Not Very Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Whatever, now that it's come to this. I'll tell you.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Inam hid all your tools inside.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: What???
attributes.name: Booze-loving Durins

attributes.content: If you don't believe me, go check it out yourself. Of course, until you defeat me, I'm not going to let you take them.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: So... That's why you leapt up there? To keep our tools from getting hit by the missiles?
attributes.name: Starting-to-be-Courteous Durin

attributes.content: So that's why you ran behind the Giant, Ultimate Ugly Thing Mk. 3? Because you were scared of the cave getting caught in the battle?
attributes.name: Starting-to-be-Astute Durin

attributes.content: That's why you tried to chase us away? Because you were afraid our tools would be caught in the weapons test?
attributes.name: Starting-to-be-Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Didn't I tell you? I asked you guys to go somewhere else for your own benefit.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Gavial... Your tail looks like it's bleeding.
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: It's no big deal.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I use my tail to pull myself up the machine. Maybe something sharp gave me a cut or something.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Your face is hurt, too.
attributes.name: Astute Durin

attributes.content: It's been a while since I've had such a great fight. Would be weird to not be hurt somewhere.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Do you want to keep going...?
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Up to you.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: If you guys are up to it, I'm all for it.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Maybe... in a few days.
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Yeah, that's probably for the better. I mean, your ultimate attacks didn't seem to work on me at all.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Of course, I'll post guards here to keep a close eye on the cave. Don't you even think about getting your stuff back without defeating me!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: You guys are here.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Oh, looks like you brought your Giant, Ultimate Ugly Thing Mk. 3 too.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: This is the Mk. 4.
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Good. Looks like technology evolves fast.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Should we get started, then?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Hold on.
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Holding the remote controller in his hand, the Durin looks at neither Gavial nor the large robot. Instead, he looks to the sky and starts mumbling.
If Gavial does this, then I'll...
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: I do this, and Gavial will...
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Gavial does that, I'll—
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: I'll...
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: The Durin freezes for a moment before drooping his head.
Should we get started now?
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: Alright, let's do this!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Gavial assumes her stance and waits for the giant machine's attack.
At that very moment, the Durin presses down on the remote in his hand.
A large explosion occurs, but Gavial finds herself unscathed.
She gapes at the robot, now nothing but a pile of scrap metal.
Wha... What the hell is this about?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: We made lots of improvements after the last battle, but our careful tests show that the Giant, Ultimate Ugly Thing series is no match for you even after all our upgrades.
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: That's why I came up with one last trick: have the Giant, Ultimate Ugly Thing Mk. 4 blow itself up.
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: But you didn't have to self-destruct the minute we start, right?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: ...I did that because I was working out what you'd do.
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: And I figured that we were never going to win even if with the self-destruct.
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: It's to show that we're accepting our defeat. I had no other choice!
attributes.name: Courteous Durin

attributes.content: But I was waiting for Zumama to turn it into an industrial robot!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Welcome back, Inam.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Welcome back!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: You two look quite cheerful.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: You came back quick. I bet everything must have gone really well!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Couldn't have been better. Thanks to the preparations we made beforehand, the Court of Sargon was absolutely not interested in Acahualla.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: So how were things here? Everything running as usual?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Yup, super normal! Gavial's keeping the Durins' alcohol ban going just fine!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Sounds like you've done well, Gavial.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: So how did it feel like, having to deal with the Durins?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Pretty good.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: They may look like a stubborn bunch that likes to fool around, but they actually aren't so bad.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: How did you stop the ones that keep clamoring for booze, then?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Mostly with my fists.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: You beat them up?!
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Gavial didn't do that! They made a promise. Anyone who manages to defeat Gavial gets their tools back, but none of them ever won!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: Oh, so that's how it was.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: ...Isn't that kind of the same thing as beating them up?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Why don't we head back first?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Inam, you're back!
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: Hello.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Come, take a look at this! This is a list of events in our competition.
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: A competition...?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: That's right! A competition!
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: I still have a business meeting with my buddies at the mead fan club, so I'll get going now. See you later!
attributes.name: Clear-headed Durin

attributes.content: The Third... Giant, Ultimate Ugly Thing Cup... Self-Driving Robots Competition Preliminaries...
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: The victor's creation will fight against Gavial... and defeating Gavial will result in the return of all alcohol making tools and equipment...
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Inam, you don't look too well. Got a headache or something?
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: To tell the truth, yes.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Never mind, I more or less expected something like this with Gavial in charge.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Let's head to the Durins' settlement. If they're having so much fun, surely they must already be done with all the construction?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Hey, isn't that Zeruertza's weather forecast chief? Is he joining in on this?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Like I said, Avdotya, I've already made it to the semifinals. I just need one more round! One more round!
attributes.name: Edge Eartheart

attributes.content: Inam? Is that you?
attributes.name: Avdotya

attributes.content: Finally, you are back! Please, help me talk some sense into Chief Edge. Ask him to get everyone to stop all this self-driving robot nonsense!
attributes.name: Avdotya

attributes.content: Gavial?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Uh, something the matter?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Don't tell me you came up with these competitions to keep the Durins from drinking.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Er... More or less?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: Then what about the Durins' settlement?!
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Look.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: A gigantic machine pulls into the area.
A few Durins, keeping a safe distance from the robot, pilot it remotely as it passes by the two of them.
What's this abomination that looks like the bastard child of the Big, Ugly Thing and their self-drivers...?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: If memory serves, they call it the 'Giant, Ultimate Ugly Thing Mk. 5.'
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: It's no match for me, but thanks to Zumama and Deculture Silvermint, it makes for a passable industrial robot.
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: If only your trip took a couple more days. We could've finished the settlement before you got back!
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: I must be dreaming.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Gavial, punch me.
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Ow!
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: This is real?
attributes.name: Inam

attributes.content: Gavial! Gavial!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: What's up?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: The preliminaries' winner has been decided, and the Durins are clamoring for you to fight their champion!
attributes.name: Tomimi

attributes.content: So, Inam, it's been a while since Acahualla last had a duel. Wanna come watch?
attributes.name: Gavial

attributes.content: My pleasure.
attributes.name: Inam
